Furniture giant IKEA has banned people from playing one of the most-loved childhood games - hide and seek.

More than 33,000 shoppers have signed up on Facebook to participate in the giant maze-like store in Tempe, inner west of Sydney on Saturday, May 23.

The event will begin from 1pm and within 10 minutes from the starting time, players are encouraged to hide in wardrobes, storage units and underneath piles of soft toys.

But the Swedish retailer has put a stop to the unofficial event after attracting tens of thousands of participants, claiming the game 'raises security issues for both customers and co-workers.'

